Review: Hadn't seen this since my first film studies class way back in highschool. Maybe 10 years ago now so I thought this warranted a rewatch all this time later. No surprise it's still a masterpiece. Every shot was a treat for the eyes with plenty to chew on.
Dudes rock. The only two women in this movie were Kurt Russel and John Carpenter's wives.

Very relatable cynicism that oozes not just from the characters but the world itself! I loved all the cheesy tv ads, the dude bro blues music, the phony feminist art pieces, perfection. And the nunchakus, my God. I could have done with 3-5 more nunchaku scenes please!
What a sleazy scary entitled lil freak.

It really struck me this watch the way it captures how it felt to be an awkward teen. Were you embarrassed by that thing you said? Oops the whole school knows it already! Girlfriend dumped you? Welp time to kill yourself! Try to talk to a new girl? Oh fuck you fucked up so bad the whole basketball team is gonna beat you up! As silly as this movie is I really do believe it has genuine heart and maybe…

Movie: Austin Powers: International Man of Mystery
Review: Totally holds up and has 2 of my favorite gags in any movie, the steamroller and the cart getting stuck in the hallway. GROOVY BAYBEEEE

The choreography and tap dancing were great of course by my goodness the COLOR wow! Super fun cheerful time tho without all the singing and dancing there is almost zero chemistry between the 2 leads. Gene Kelly's character is kind of a pretentious jerk? Actually all of the men are??? And the film isn't interested in making any kind of statement about it, everyone's just kinda cool with it?

Truly a unique movie that has often been imitated but never replicated. It manages to be so authentically emo while having BANGER song after BANGER song. If my brother didn't already make this movie his whole personality in high school I probably would have. I'll watch it every year or so during the holidays for the rest of my life.

There's a lot I found clunky and confusing about it tbh! And not confusing in a dreamlike cool way cus there's plenty of that too which I like. The pacing was pretty off and parts of the story made no sense to me. Maybe another watch or reading the source material will help. The central themes of death, grief, legacy, letting go, all great stuff and I think represented well through the visuals and world building but NOT through it's…
SO CUTE. So much character building, you can tell so much by what they say and what they don't say to each other. A perfect pair of grifters, I hope they get that piano factory.
Even with the cool fencing scene it's hard to justify a plot so bad, so boring yet at the same time so hilariously offensive. Almost as offensive as that Madonna track heyooooooo.

More low budget comedy movies please! Well ok there probably still are plenty of those being made these days but the writing is so BAD no one knows how to make comedy movies lately!I'm convinced if some indie director made special effort to replicate the tone and humor / writing style of Caddyshack we'd have a modern comedy hit. Kinda like stranger things did for fantasy horror. Fuck it, copy all the characters too. Paul Rudd as Chevy surragote,…
